<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1401" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1401">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/271.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-12">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 12, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The Minister of Spain to
                                Mexico wires me that the Spanish colony of the port of Guaymas
                                consisting of about two hundred persons is completely shut out from
                                communication with our representative at the capital of the
                                neighboring Republic and fears that it may be left without adequate
                                protection if the town should be taken by the revolutionists.</p>
                            <p>In view thereof I have recourse to your excellency’s courtesy and beg
                                you kindly to instruct the Consul of the United States at Guaymas,
                                Sonora, Mexico, to protect the said Spanish subjects when
                                necessary.</p>
                            <p>Thanking your excellency in advance, I avail [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>